definitions.definition: The office , position , rank , or title of a voivode ( “ a local ruler or official in various parts of central and eastern Europe ; an administrative chief in modern Poland ” ) .
The jurisdiction of a voivode, comparable to a countship or a county .
The highest - level administrative subdivision of Poland , comparable to a province or state .
